​
   1.2    These terms and conditions govern how the User shall use any of Our Products. Under no circumstances will the User be exempt from any of the terms listed in the page, or listed elsewhere in a non-modified version of one of our Products.
​
   1.3    By using Our Products, you fully accept Our terms and conditions. If you do not accept Our terms and conditions, you may not use Our Products, nor may you contain copies of them.
​
   1.4    If the User chooses to use Our Products, and create an account with Us, we have full rights to access the User's information such as: their respective email, username, password, computer information, physical and digital address, etc. We will not share the User's information with any one, and this information will be used purely for development purposes. Registration with any of Our Products means you agree to Our terms of service in full. If asked by law enforcement to provide information we will provide the information available which is deemed necessary by law.
​
   1.5    Our website uses cookies, and by using Our website you agree to Our terms and conditions, and give consent to our use of cookies.

   1.6    Be aware, that at any given time, We are able to delete your content, whether it is your account settings, personal information, data stored in Our Public User Database, etc. We, however, have no way of reading the User’s messages sent to our servers, and the User’s chat(s) will be treated confidentially in all senses. Knowledge of the User’s password and two-factor authentication code is the only way to gain access to the messages sent and received by them through Affix Services, and Team Affix and law enforcement may request them.

